                <h1>Boosting Comprehension: The Role of Background Knowledge in Learning</h1>
                <p>Students with greater background knowledge of a text's topic are more likely to engage deeply with the material. They can better understand context, make connections to prior knowledge, and critically analyze content. This enhanced comprehension leads to improved retention, higher academic performance, and a greater enjoyment of learning.</p>
